你仍在折磨布林汉姆？
You still torturing Bringham?

67
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:14,146
这么说吧，我不像他那么看重哈佛学位
Nick: Let's just say I'm less impressed with his Harvard degree than he is.

68
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,647
呵，我们不能都去上福德汉姆
Well, we can't all have gone to Fordham.

69
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:17,065
我上过福德汉姆夜校
I went to Fordham night school.

70
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,443
知道我在福德汉姆夜校学到什么了吗？
You know what I learned in Fordham night school?

71
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,902
法学院里学不到什么法律
Law school's got nothing to do with law.

72
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,322
我猜你逃了职场哲学的课
Guess you skipped the course on inter-office politics.

73
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:26,241
我所需要的就是陪审团喜欢我 这不是你教我的吗，乔纳斯？
All I need is a jury to like me. Isn't that what you told me, Jonas?

74
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:29,286
谢尔顿案件… 进展到哪了？
The Shelton case- where are we?

75
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:31,163
昨晚出了点差错，伯奇法官那边
It went sideways last night- Judge Burch.

76
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,706
啊…
Ahh.

77
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:34,666
坏消息，现在怎样办？
Bad news. What now?

78
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,544
- 作笔交易吧 - 尼克，他们杀了小女孩
- Let's make the deal. - They killed a little girl, Nick.

79
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:40,589
- 这是一个不完美的体制 - 而我们是不完美公仆
- It's an imperfect system. - And we its imperfect servants.

80
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:44,343
- 不过，你还是可以赢下这个案子 - 不，不能去冒险
- However you could win this case. - No, can't take that chance.

81
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:47,137
有一些公正总比没有公正好
Some justice is better than no justice at all.

82
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,306
那你得去告诉那位丈夫
You need to tell the husband.

83
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:51,683
好的 那是我的工作
Okay. That's part of my job.

84
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:54,811
很好，因为他正在等着你，现在！
Good, because he's waiting for you right now.

85
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:56,646
什么？
What?

86
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:08,825
- 你怎么样？ - 还好，你怎么样？
- How are you doing? - Good. How are you doing?

87
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:11,578
还好 坐吧，坐吧
Good. Sit. Sit.

88
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:14,247
呃，一直没有你的消息
Well, I didn't hear back from you

89
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:17,584
所以我写了一些东西关于这案子
and made some notes on the case.

90
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,670
我有些好主意
I had some good ideas.

91
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,506
好，让我来看看
Yeah, let me take a look at it.

92
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,884
恩，它们只是…
Well, they're just-

93
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:33,517
我正打算跟你谈这个
I was gonna talk to you about those.

94
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,895
你信任我么？
Do you trust me?

95
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,942
你信任我么，克莱德？
Do you trust me, Clyde?

96
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:44,694
是的，当然
Yeah, of course.

97
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:50,575
多比同意作证检举阿米
Darby has agreed to testify against Ames.

98
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:53,328
有了多比的证词
With Darby's testimony,

99
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,288
阿米就会被判死刑
Ames will go to death row.

100
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:03,296
嗯，那…多比会怎样？
Um, what about- what about Darby then?

101
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:06,967
多比将被定罪谋杀
Darby will plead guilty to murder.

102
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:09,803
- 几级？ - 三级
- In what degree? - Third.

103
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:12,431
他会服刑多久？五年？
He serves, what? Five years...

104
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:15,183
最多？
at best?

105
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,228
很抱歉，我不明白
I don't understand. I'm sorry.

106
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:22,232
我们遇到了麻烦 法官裁定DNA证据不被采用
We had a setback. The judge ruled that the DNA was inadmissible.

107
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,360
- 什么？ - 非法证据排除原则
- What? - Exclusionary rule.

108
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:27,362
辩方律师的伎俩
The opposing counsel maneuvered it.

109
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,698
你说过这个部分容易辨认
You said this part of the case was clear-cut.

110
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,366
我们在他的衬衫上发现了血迹
We had the blood on his shirt-

111
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,201
这也涵盖在同样的原则下
It's covered under the same rule.

112
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:34,703
那法医的其它证据呢？
What about the rest of the forensic evidence?

113
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:38,498
那些都不是决定性的，克莱德
It's not conclusive, Clyde.

114
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:44,087
好吧，没关系 我看见…我看见他们的脸了
Okay, that's okay. 'Cause I saw- I saw their faces.

115
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,299
我亲眼看到他们行凶 他们杀了我的小女儿，尼克
I saw them do it. I mean, he killed my little girl, Nick.

116
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,343
克莱德，你晕过去了 你的证词无法令人信服
You blacked out, Clyde. Your testimony won't be reliable.

117
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:53,263
你站上证人席时 辩方律师会把你撕碎的
You get on the stand and the defense will tear you apart.

118
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:55,849
不，不，陪审团会相信我的
No no, the jury's gonna believe me though.

119
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:59,144
- 因为这就是真相，我们可以… - 我们会输的
- Because it's the truth! We can- - We can lose.

120
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:02,063
然后我们会一无所获
And then we'd have nothing.

121
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:04,608
你会浪费一整年的时间 花费百万美元
You will waste a whole year, spend millions of dollars,

122
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,693
然后他俩双双逍遥法外
and then both of them could end up going free.

123
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:10,405
尼克，他们都有罪 尤其是多比！
Nick, both of them are guilty, especially Darby!

124
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,574
- 你知道这些 - 这与你知道什么无关，克莱德
- You know that. - It's not what you know, Clyde.

125
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,160
而是你能在法庭上证明什么
It's what you can prove in court.

126
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,416
请别与这人做这个交易
Please don't make a deal with this man.

127
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:23,627
请别与这人交易，他是禽兽
Please don't make a deal with this man. He's a monster-

128
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,296
对不起，协议已经达成了，对不起
I'm sorry, the deal is done. I'm sorry.

129
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,298
我达成了协议
I made the deal.

130
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:31,426
什么？你怎么可以那样做？
What? How could you do that?

131
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:35,180
这就是司法体系运作的方式
This is just how the justice system works.

132
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:39,434
听着，我知道你现在不认可这点
Listen, I know you don't think it right now,

133
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:42,354
但这其实是我们的胜利
but this is a victory for us.

134
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,276
你们办公室已经认可这个协议了吗？
Woman: Your office has certified this agreement?

135
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,694
是的，法官阁下
Yes, Your Honor.

136
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:53,740
雷诺斯先生，今天有无高见与法庭分享？
Mr. Reynolds, any great insights to share with the court today?

137
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,910
我是辩方律师，法官阁下 我没多少高见
I'm a defense attorney, Your Honor. I don't have many of those.

138
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:03,166
没有，法官大人，没有意见了
No, Your Honor. No insights.

139
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:06,127
很好，那我相信我们可以毫无阻碍地
Good, then I trust that we can move forward with Mr. Ames's trial

140
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:09,798
推进阿米先生的判决了 审批日期将近了
unimpeded by continuances. A triaI date is imminent.

141
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,761
喂？
Yeah?

142
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,305
瑞斯先生，我的法庭不允许讲手机
There's no cell phones in my courtroom, Mr. Rice.

143
00:09:17,473 --> 00:09:18,807
- 我们说过了… - 抱歉
- We've been over this- - I'm sorry.

144
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:20,100
一遍地，又一遍地
- and over this, over this...

145
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,936
是的，我有些急事…
Yeah, I had some exigent business I-

146
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,063
下次我就要没收了
Next time it's mine.

147
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,736
- 啊，你结婚了吗？ - 你说什么？
- Ah, you married? - Excuse me?

148
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:33,905
你结婚了？
Are you married?

149
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:39,035
请继续喷 这样我就能毁了你
Please fuck this up so I can destroy you.

150
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:46,876
我不想害人
I wish ill for no man,

151
00:09:47,044 --> 00:09:50,714
不过阿米罪有应得
but Ames deserves to suffer for what he did.

152
00:09:50,881 --> 00:09:54,050
我是说，你没法跟天斗的对吧？
I mean, you can't fight fate, right?

153
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,266
尼克
Nick.

154
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:04,019
一旦你做了决定 就要学会接受…继续往前
Cantrell: Once you make a decision, live with it- move on.

155
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:06,354
这份工作，最大的资产就是短暂记忆
This job, your best asset's a short memory.

156
00:10:06,522 --> 00:10:09,566
别自责了，其他很多人都这样干了
Don't beat yourself up. Too many other people out there doing that already.

157
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:10,984
看，现在那边就有一些人
Look, there's some of them right now.

158
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:14,112
是不是到了时间你要给我讲些寓言
Isn't this where you tell me some type of old fable

159
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,073
或者启蒙故事的了
or wives' tale-

160
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:19,075
好了，好了，我想到一个了
All right, all right, I got one.

161
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:21,161
当马可・奥勒留走过罗马时代广场时
Marcus Aurelius hired a servant to walk behind him

162
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:22,912
他雇了一个仆人跟在身后
as he made his way through the Roman town square.

163
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:25,165
这个仆人唯一的工作就是
And this servant's only job

164
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,001
当别人赞美他时，在他耳边低声说
was to whisper in his ear when people praised him,

165
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:31,463
你只是个凡人 你只是个凡人
"You're only a man. You're only a man. "

166
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,048
- 好了，凡人 - 好吧，凡人
