00:55:49,404 --> 00:55:51,905
你的幸运日，啊？ 有东西吃
Your lucky day, huh? Get some food.

837
00:55:52,073 --> 00:55:54,950
这里，要拍张照吗？
Here, wanna take a shot at this?

838
00:55:55,118 --> 00:55:57,244
- 这是什么？ - 知道怎么用吗？
- What is it? - Know how to use it?

839
00:55:57,412 --> 00:55:59,663
不知道
No.

840
00:56:16,431 --> 00:56:19,308
哦，该死，快看
Inmate: Oh, shit! Check this out!

841
00:56:22,395 --> 00:56:24,646
他疯了
He's crazy!

842
00:56:24,814 --> 00:56:26,315
现在别停下，伙计
Don't stop now, partner!

843
00:56:26,483 --> 00:56:29,318
干掉他，快！ 把他头割下来
Finish him, come on! Take his head off!

844
00:56:29,486 --> 00:56:33,739
割下来
Take it off!

845
00:57:03,561 --> 00:57:05,938
我需要洗个澡，典狱长
I need a shower, Warden.

846
00:57:06,105 --> 00:57:07,314
把他弄出去
Get him out of there!

847
00:57:10,860 --> 00:57:13,320
唐尼根，你的表几点了？
Nick: Dunnigan, what time do you have?

848
00:57:15,573 --> 00:57:16,865
1点37分
37.

849
00:57:17,033 --> 00:57:18,825
到这里我们大约花了15分钟
Took us roughly 15 minutes to get here.

850
00:57:18,993 --> 00:57:20,077
是吗？
Yeah?

851
00:57:20,245 --> 00:57:22,746
雷诺斯的氧气被设定在1点15分关闭
Reynolds's air was rigged to shut off at 1:15.

852
00:57:22,914 --> 00:57:25,666
如果谢尔顿能准时吃到午餐 他应该能活着
If Shelton would have got his lunch on time, he'd still be alive.

853
00:57:25,833 --> 00:57:27,125
去他妈的，尼克
Fuck this guy, Nick.

854
00:57:27,293 --> 00:57:31,046
他想要玩游戏 我们也可以跟他玩
He wants to play games, we can play games too.

855
00:57:31,214 --> 00:57:33,549
我们得把手套摘下来
We need to take the gloves off.

856
00:57:33,716 --> 00:57:35,425
不行
No.

857
00:57:39,556 --> 00:57:42,599
尼克，我是莎拉 听着，克莱德杀了他的牢友
Nick, it's Sarah. Listen, Clyde murdered his cell-mate.

858
00:57:42,767 --> 00:57:46,645
典狱长大发雷霆，要把他移至禁闭室
The warden is furious. He's moving him to solitary.

859
00:57:46,813 --> 00:57:49,064
目前我就只知道这些
That's all I know right now.

860
00:58:19,929 --> 00:58:22,764
目前什么情况？
How are we doing?

861
00:58:22,932 --> 00:58:25,851
不错，你能相信吗？
Great. Can you believe this?

862
00:58:26,019 --> 00:58:29,146
把他iPod拆了找线索
Checking his iPod for clues.

863
00:58:29,314 --> 00:58:30,856
我对我女儿也这么做
I do the same thing with my daughter's.

864
00:58:31,024 --> 00:58:32,733
有收获吗？
Learn anything?

865
00:58:32,900 --> 00:58:35,319
恩，他们都听垃圾音乐
Yeah, they both got shit taste in music.

866
00:58:37,363 --> 00:58:39,740
我们有招术跟这个家伙玩了吗？
We got a game plan with this guy or what?

867
00:58:39,907 --> 00:58:41,491
招术？
Game plan?

868
00:58:41,659 --> 00:58:43,535
我跟你说，我有个招术
I tell you, I got a game plan.

869
00:58:43,703 --> 00:58:46,413
给我跟他五分钟时间 我会搞残这个混蛋
Give me five minutes alone with him and I'll cripple the fucker.

870
00:58:46,581 --> 00:58:49,583
我才不管他家庭发生了什么
I don't give a shit what happened to his family.

871
00:58:49,751 --> 00:58:51,209
没有借口
It's no excuse.

872
00:58:58,301 --> 00:58:59,885
哇
Wow.

873
00:59:07,018 --> 00:59:08,685
就在这
Stop right there.

874
00:59:17,362 --> 00:59:19,071
进屋去
Step into the cell.

875
01:00:05,284 --> 01:00:07,746
我们发现雷诺斯了
We found Reynolds.

876
01:00:07,781 --> 01:00:10,833
当赶到时太迟了
Moments too late, from what I hear.

877
01:00:10,876 --> 01:00:14,961
我必须打给他老婆 告诉她丈夫被活埋了
I had to call his wife and tell her that her husband had been buried alive.

878
01:00:15,002 --> 01:00:17,793
司法制度需要严厉，尼克
Justice should be harsh, Nick,

879
01:00:17,831 --> 01:00:20,486
尤其是对于那种对他人拒绝公正的人
but especially for those who denied it to others.

880
01:00:20,528 --> 01:00:23,183
杀你的牢友呢？怎么回事？
And your cell-mate? What was that about?

881
01:00:26,817 --> 01:00:29,903
你杀死这人就是因为午餐来迟了
You murdered a man because your lunch was late.

882
01:00:29,946 --> 01:00:31,909
不
No.

883
01:00:31,943 --> 01:00:36,233
不，不，是你杀了他 因为你没有信守承诺
No. No, you murdered him because you couldn't keep your word.

884
01:00:36,271 --> 01:00:39,629
我们达成了协议，你和我 下午1点
We made a deal, you and I: 00 PM.

885
01:00:39,665 --> 01:00:42,854
那是一个非常重要的原则 我希望你能开始学会，尼克
That's a pretty important principle I'd like you start learning, Nick:

886
01:00:42,894 --> 01:00:44,948
- 遵守你的诺言 - 哦，真的吗？
- keeping your word. - Oh, really?

887
01:00:44,991 --> 01:00:47,975
当你折磨并杀死那些人时 你又在按什么原则行事
What principle was at work when you tortured and killed those people?

888
01:00:48,018 --> 01:00:51,706
那就是每个人都应该为自己的行为负责
That everyone must be held accountable for their actions.

889
01:00:57,804 --> 01:01:00,707
你以为你的妻子女儿 对你以她们的名义杀人
You think your wife and daughter would feel good

890
01:01:00,757 --> 01:01:03,592
会感觉很好吗？
about you killing in their name?

891
01:01:29,322 --> 01:01:32,943
我妻子和女儿再也没有感觉了
My wife and daughter can't feeI anything.

892
01:01:34,248 --> 01:01:36,234
他们死了
They're dead.

893
01:02:12,203 --> 01:02:14,297
嘿，尼克
Hey, Nick?

894
01:02:14,330 --> 01:02:16,665
查克莱德的不动产一事 史坦菲德法官拒绝了我们
On Clyde's real estate, Judge Stansfield shut us down.

895
01:02:16,833 --> 01:02:20,293
他在寻找某个合法案例 我不知道是否存在
He's looking for some sort of legal precedent that I'm not sure exists.

896
01:02:20,461 --> 01:02:21,503
- 但？ - 但…
- But? - But...

897
01:02:21,671 --> 01:02:22,963
我想我可能找到了其它方法
I think I may have found a way around it.

898
01:02:23,130 --> 01:02:25,298
- 我要找一个朋友帮忙 - 你的朋友是谁？
- I'll call in a favor from a friend. - Who's your friend?

899
01:02:25,466 --> 01:02:27,634
不能透露朋友的名字 不然他们不会帮忙
You don't name your friends or they stop doing you favors.

900
01:02:27,802 --> 01:02:29,469
坎特雷尔还说了什么
Something else Cantrell said.

901
01:02:29,637 --> 01:02:33,640
没有，就这些了 乔纳斯，你好
No, that was all you. Jonas, hi.

902
01:02:34,684 --> 01:02:37,769
她思考的模式和你一样，尼克 我看你把她训练得很不错
She's thinking just like you, Nick. Guess you trained her well.

903
01:02:37,937 --> 01:02:40,939
- 有天她会坐上我的位子 - 我们透透气去吧
- One day she'll have my job. - Let's get some air.

904
01:02:43,985 --> 01:02:46,319
克莱德的政府契约款困扰着我
Clyde's government contract payments were bothering me,

905
01:02:46,487 --> 01:02:49,072
因此我动用了一些旧关系 我们要见个人
so I pulled some ancient strings. We're meeting someone.

906
01:02:49,240 --> 01:02:50,699
会是谁呢？
Who might that be?

907
01:02:50,867 --> 01:02:54,703
那些做真正下流事情的人 所以我们才能够住着美国梦
Someone who does some really nasty shit so we can live the American dream.

908
01:03:06,883 --> 01:03:08,842
那么克莱德终于疯了吗？
So Clyde finally lost it?

909
01:03:09,010 --> 01:03:11,136
一定是有人真的惹毛他了
Somebody must have really pissed him off.

910
01:03:11,304 --> 01:03:13,638
你和谢尔顿一起工作过？对吧？
You worked with Shelton, is that right?

911
01:03:13,806 --> 01:03:17,517
首先，我从没来过这里 我们也从没有对过话
Okay, first of all, I was never here and we never spoke.

912
01:03:17,685 --> 01:03:20,312
告诉我们在对付谁 谢尔顿是间谍还是…
Tell us what we're dealing with. Shelton was a spy or-

913
01:03:20,479 --> 01:03:23,064
间谍太稀松平常了 我就是间谍
Spies are a dime a dozen. I'm a spy.

914
01:03:23,232 --> 01:03:26,735
克莱德是天才 他是会动脑筋那个
Clyde is a brain. He's a think-tank type guy.

915
01:03:26,903 --> 01:03:29,404
他的专长是低速冲击动力操作
His specialty was low-impact kinetic operations.

916
01:03:29,572 --> 01:03:31,948
这是他杀人一种美化的说法吗？
Is this a hell of a fancy way to say that he kills people?

917
01:03:32,116 --> 01:03:33,241
我们杀人
We kill people.

918
01:03:33,409 --> 01:03:35,911
他可以不共处一室就能干出来
He figured out how to do it without ever being in the same room.

919
01:03:36,078 --> 01:03:39,414
这是他的天赋，而且他是最优秀的
It was his gift, and he was the best.

920
01:03:39,582 --> 01:03:42,000
有次我们对付一个狡猾的目标
One time we're tasking this tricky target.

921
01:03:42,168 --> 01:03:44,669
我们用巡航导弹、猛禽战机
I mean, we're using cruise missiles and predators

922
01:03:44,837 --> 01:03:48,632
甚至动用了B2隐形轰炸机 飞到这家伙的别墅去炸他
and we even had a B-2 bomber flatten this guy's villa with a JDAM.

923
01:03:48,799 --> 01:03:50,425
我们循规蹈矩的方法浪费了数百万
All right? We're burning up millions in ordnance

924
01:03:50,593 --> 01:03:51,927
连这家伙的影子都没有见到
and we're getting nowhere with this guy.

925
01:03:52,094 --> 01:03:55,013
所以我们找来了克莱德 请他解决这个问题
So we call Clyde and we ask him to solve our problem.

926
01:03:55,181 --> 01:03:57,098
克莱德发明一项高强力缝线
Clyde develops a Kevlar thread

927
01:03:57,266 --> 01:03:59,935
有着碳纤维制的高科技制轮装置
with a high-tech ratchet made of carbon fiber

928
01:04:00,102 --> 01:04:01,978
能够安装在领带里
put in a necktie.

929
01:04:02,146 --> 01:04:04,731
两天后，坏蛋太太回到家
Two days later, Mrs. Bad Guy comes home,

930
01:04:04,899 --> 01:04:07,609
发现坏蛋先生倒在浴室的瓷砖上
finds Mr. Bad Guy dead on the bathroom tile,

931
01:04:07,777 --> 01:04:09,110
窒息而死
choked to death.

932
01:04:10,905 --> 01:04:13,782
我所说的是，只能假设这家伙可以
What I'm saying is, just assume that this guy can hear and see

933
01:04:13,950 --> 01:04:15,617
听到或看到你的一举一动
everything that you're doing.

934
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:17,911
不，我们把他关起来了 高度戒备中
Nick: No, we've got him locked away, maximum security.

935
01:04:18,079 --> 01:04:21,081
如果他在监狱，那是因为他想在狱中
Man: If he's in jail, it's because he wants to be in jail.

936
01:04:21,248 --> 01:04:24,918
他是个天生的战略家 他的每个行动都有意义
He's a born tactician. Every move that he makes, it means something.

937
01:04:25,962 --> 01:04:28,421
他杀死牢友，你以为是随意的吗？
That cell-mate that he killed- you think that was random?

938
01:04:30,049 --> 01:04:31,758
不是
No.

939
01:04:31,926 --> 01:04:34,552
那只是棋盘上被摆布的一个棋子
That's a pawn being moved off the board.

940
01:04:36,138 --> 01:04:38,974
换作我，我会找出下一个目标
If I were you, I'd be looking for the next piece.

941
01:04:39,141 --> 01:04:41,810
和那案子有关联的每个人
Anybody who had anything to do with that case,

942
01:04:41,978 --> 01:04:43,979
他不会放过你们的
he's gonna be coming after you.

943
01:04:44,981 --> 01:04:49,192
那你的意思是？ 你是说我们无法阻止他？
So what are you saying? You saying we can't stop him?

944
01:04:51,278 --> 01:04:54,114
走进他的牢房 给他脑袋一颗子弹
Walk into his cell and put a bullet in his head.

945
01:04:55,992 --> 01:04:58,952
除此之外？ 别无他法，你无法阻止他
Aside from that? No, you can't stop him.

946
01:04:59,120 --> 01:05:01,638
如果克莱德想要你死，你就死
If Clyde wants you dead, you're dead.

947
01:05:13,050 --> 01:05:16,052
- 你好 - 莎拉？莎拉，是尼克
- Hello? - Sarah? Sarah, it's Nick.

948
01:05:16,220 --> 01:05:17,971
安排和伯奇法官会个面
Set up a meeting with Judge Burch.

949
01:05:18,139 --> 01:05:20,140
我们得让她帮我们把克莱德监押起来
We need her to help us keep Clyde on ice.

950
01:05:20,307 --> 01:05:22,934
帮我们做什么？尼克 他已经在牢里了
Help us with what, Nick? The man's in prison.

951
01:05:23,102 --> 01:05:24,811
他比我们想象的更可怕
He's worse than we thought.

952
01:05:24,979 --> 01:05:27,439
- 切斯特是你的男朋友，对吧？ - 切斯特
- Chester's your boyfriend, right? - Chester.

953
01:05:27,606 --> 01:05:29,441
是的
Yeah.

954
01:05:29,608 --> 01:05:32,819
很好，也许去他那待几天
Good. Maybe stay a few days at his place.

955
01:05:32,987 --> 01:05:36,031
再叫唐尼派辆巡逻车到我家来
And have Dunnigan send a patroI car to my house.

956
01:05:36,198 --> 01:05:37,949
对此很抱歉，莎拉
Sorry about this, Sarah.

957
01:05:45,166 --> 01:05:47,417
我不能取代刑法
Judge Burch: I can't supersede the penal code.

958
01:05:47,585 --> 01:05:49,044
你们已经把他关入禁闭室
You've already got him in solitary.

959
01:05:49,211 --> 01:05:51,463
到下周随便一个律师助理就会让他出来
A half-decent paralegal will have him out of there by next week.

960
01:05:51,630 --> 01:05:53,298
我们只想限制他的选择
We just want to limit his options;

961
01:05:53,466 --> 01:05:55,133
减少他的联系，减少渠道
give him less contact, less access,

962
01:05:55,316 --> 01:05:58,651
即使只是解除他一个星期的委托权
even if it's just rescinding his mandatory exercise period for a week.

963
01:05:58,688 --> 01:06:01,089
- 用什么名义？ - 什么都可以
- Under what cause? - Whatever cause you want.

964
01:06:01,125 --> 01:06:03,390
随便用什么法条
Wrap it around whatever piece of legal doctrine

965
01:06:03,429 --> 01:06:07,093
只要能合理化这个即可，法官大人
that helps you rationalize it, Your Honor.

966
01:06:08,736 --> 01:06:10,204
那么，我直说吧
So let me get this straight:

967
01:06:10,238 --> 01:06:13,072
你们想要我侵犯上帝赋予他的权利？
you want me to violate his God-given civil rights

968
01:06:13,109 --> 01:06:15,874
以某种罪恶第六感的名义
in the name of some murky sense of the greater good.

969
01:06:15,913 --> 01:06:18,007
先生们，是这个意思吗？
Is that the gist of it, gentlemen?

970
01:06:24,826 --> 01:06:27,387
好吧，我入伙
Okay. I'm game.

971
01:06:28,398 --> 01:06:32,529
只是别想持续太久，好吗？
Just don't plan on it sticking for long, all right?

972
01:06:36,075 --> 01:06:37,805
等会，你要接电话？
Wait, you're gonna take that,

973
01:06:37,845 --> 01:06:40,007
你训斥过我接电话的事情
after all the grief you've given me over cell phones?

974
01:06:40,048 --> 01:06:43,280
那是当法官的好处之一，瑞斯先生
That's one of the benefits of being a judge, Mr. Rice.

975
01:06:43,319 --> 01:06:46,346
我相当可以随心所欲
I can pretty much do whatever I want.

976
01:06:48,726 --> 01:06:50,194
喂？
Hello?

977
01:06:52,732 --> 01:06:54,530
哦，上帝
Oh my God.

978
01:06:54,568 --> 01:06:57,231
退后，退后
Nick: Back out. Back out.

979
01:07:00,032 --> 01:07:03,993
…在市政厅，尽管还无法证实这些细节
Female reporter:... at city hall, though we are unable to confirm the details,

980
01:07:04,161 --> 01:07:06,287
但我们知道至少一人死亡
we do know that at least one person is dead

981
01:07:06,455 --> 01:07:08,581
官方称很可能是谋杀
in what officials are calling a possible murder.

982
01:07:08,749 --> 01:07:11,000
我们会有记者继续…
We have reporters on the ground...

983
01:07:11,168 --> 01:07:12,418
上来
Up.

984
01:07:17,508 --> 01:07:19,342
有人在帮这家伙
Somebody's helping this guy-

985
01:07:19,510 --> 01:07:21,761
手机里的炸弹 而她毫不知情
a bomb in that phone, and she doesn't know about it.

986
01:07:21,929 --> 01:07:24,889
谁能做到呢？
Who had access?

987
01:07:25,057 --> 01:07:26,766
你还好吗？
Are you okay?

988
01:07:26,934 --> 01:07:29,602
我是战争里过来的，还有两个前妻 我没事的
I've survived the war and two ex-wives. I'll be fine.

989
01:07:31,605 --> 01:07:33,439
你还好吗？
How are you holding up?

990
01:07:33,607 --> 01:07:35,900
我还好
I'm good.

991
01:07:51,667 --> 01:07:53,794
现在你把法官也杀了？
So you're killing judges now?

992
01:07:53,836 --> 01:07:58,034
以我的经验来看，尼克 只有血的教训才能持久
In my experience, Nick, lessons not learned in blood are soon forgotten.

993
01:07:58,073 --> 01:08:00,872
复仇能让你在晚上得到温暖吗
And vengeance keeps you warm at night.

994
01:08:00,910 --> 01:08:02,707
复仇？
Vengeance?

995
01:08:04,547 --> 01:08:07,573
这就是你所认为的吗？复仇？
That's what you think this is about? Vengeance?

996
01:08:07,617 --> 01:08:09,448
还会是什么呢？
What else could it be?

997
01:08:09,485 --> 01:08:13,786
不，尼克，我有10年的时间可以复仇 如果我要做的话
No, Nick, I had 10 years for vengeance, if that's what I wanted.

